.SH "NAME"
brlcad \- BRL\-CAD programs for solid modeling, raytracing, graphics, and image processing
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
.sp
The BRL\-CAD Distribution contains many directories of materials
(programs, man pages, documents, libraries, etc.). The major
categories of programs are:
.sp
\fImged\fP
.RS 4
A multi\-device interactive editor for constructing and
updating combinatorial solid geometry (CSG) models. See
\fBmged\fP(1), and see also \fIUnderstanding the
Preparation and Analysis of Solid Models\fP by Michael John Muuss
(enclosed, in the "paper" directory).
.RE
.sp
\fIlibrt\fP
.RS 4
A library of functions suitable for interrogation of a CSG
solid model, utilizing ray\-tracing techniques. See
\fBlibrt\fP(3).
.RE
.sp
\fIrt\fP
.RS 4
A ray\-tracing lighting model, for rendering pictures of
\fBmged\fP(1) CSG models. See
\fBrt\fP(1), \fBrtray\fP(1),
\fBrtpp\fP(1).
.RE
.sp
\fIconv\fP
.RS 4
Programs to convert \fBmged\fP(1) and
\fBpix\fP(3) format binary files to a portable ASCII
form, and back again. See \fBasc2g\fP(1),
\fBasc2pix\fP(1),
\fBconv\-vg2g\fP(1),
\fBg2asc\fP(1),
\fBpix2asc\fP(1).
.RE
.sp
\fIlibpkg\fP
.RS 4
A "message\-passing" interface layered on top of TCP
network links, to ease construction of network\-distributed
applications.
.RE
.sp
\fIlibfb\fP
.RS 4
A generic frame\-buffer library which includes support for a
number of display devices, as well as file, network, and debugging
interfaces. Most programs which use this library have the letters "fb"
in their names.  To override your system default frame\-buffer, the
environment variable \f(CRFB_FILE\fP can be set.  In addition, some
commands also support a \fB\-F\fP \fIframebuffer\fP option. Note that
the disk file format of \fIlibfb\fP is that of
\fBpix\fP(5), allowing "framebuffer" files to be
later processed by any of the "pix" family of programs. See
\fBlibfb\fP(3),
\fBpix\-fb\fP(3),
\fBpix\fP(5), etc.
.RE
.sp
\fIfbserv\fP
.RS 4
TCP\-based network server which implements remote
frame\-buffer services.
.RE
.sp
\fIlibtermio\fP
.RS 4
A library to handle terminal mode setting on both
Berkeley or SystemV machines.
.RE
.sp
\fIlibplot3\fP
.RS 4
A public\-domain version of the UNIX\-Plot library which
differs from that of the standard
\fBlibplot\fP(3), by the addition of 3\-D
primitives, color, floating point coordinate routines, and the use of
a file pointer parameter. See \fBlibplot3\fP(3),
\fBplot3\fP(5).
.RE
.sp
\fIlibrle\fP
.RS 4
A Run\-Length\-Encoding (RLE) library, providing functions
originally from the University of Utah in a library package. Note that
the current version of this library reads Edition\-3 RLE files. See
\fBrle\-fb\fP(1),
\fBfb\-rle\fP(1),
\fBrle\-pix\fP(1),
\fBpix\-rle\fP(1),
\fBlibrle\fP(3).
.RE
